node.text: Naomi Osaka has pledged to donate any prize money she wins from an upcoming tournament to help relief efforts following Saturday's 7.2-magnitude earthquake in Haiti, which has killed over 700 people. 🙏 "Really hurts to see all the devastation that's going on in Haiti, and I feel like we really can't catch a break," the 23-year-old tennis star, whose father is from Haiti, wrote.
